To: The Accreditation Committee of the Statistical Society of Canada
From: Peter Macdonald, D.Phil., P.Stat.
Date: 2010-01-30
Re: Submission of McMaster University Courses for Accreditation Status

On behalf of the Department of Mathematics and Statistics, McMaster
University, I am pleased to submit our list of courses for accreditation
status.

Our covering letter signed by the Dean, Chair and three Statistics faculty
members is attached, as is a document aligning our courses with the
checklist for A.Stat. applicants.

Information about the courses listed there, including the Calendar
descriptions and recent course outlines and final examination papers, is
posted at http://www.math.mcmaster.ca/peter/McMasterAccreditation/.

I am expecting one or two McMaster graduates to be applying for A.Stat. at
this time and this information will be of use to you in evaluating their
applications.

Please contact me if anything is not clear.

Thank you for your attention.

-- 
 Peter D.M. Macdonald, D.Phil., P.Stat.
 Professor of Math & Statistics
 McMaster University
 Hamilton, Ontario, Canada L8S 4K1



